      rawContext = "\nmacro_GuiSetText(\"NPCSAY.npcsay\", claver)\nmacro_GuiSetWinVisable(\"NPCSAY\", 1)claver=\"#0<00>¡¡¡¡You young people are so rushed. There are too many ways to get out. The simplest one is shout DuDu to the guard, It¡¯s the sign for eating. Then they will give you the food, you can take the chance to get out!!\\n\\n\"\n\nclaver=claver..\"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n#2<02><4003><0>If it's that simple, why don't you get out?\"\n\nmacro_GuiSetText(\"NPCSAY.npcsay\", claver)\nmacro_GuiSetWinVisable(\"NPCSAY\", 1)claver=\"#0<00>¡¡¡¡That¡¯s why you young people don¡¯t know how to enjoy the life. When I was here, the Longicorn king always played chess with me. I really enjoyed those days. Look at your head! Is that a scar? Do you get defeated by the mirror used by Longicorn King?\\n\\n\"\n\nclaver=claver..\"\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n#2<02><4004><0>Do you know about that mirror?\"\n\nmacro_GuiSetText(\"NPCSAY.npcsay\", claver)\nmacro_GuiSetWinVisable(\"NPCSAY\", 1)claver=\"#0<00>¡¡¡¡Of course I know. There are two mirrors, the Yang one and the Ying one. The one defeated you must be that Yang mirror. These two mirrors are very powerful and can destroy anything. You wouldn¡¯t be here if Longicorn King didn¡¯t suck that seriously. The only enemy of these mirrors is their counterpart. Ying¡¯s enemy is Yang, Yang¡¯s enemy is Ying.\\n     Longicorn King carries one mirror every day. The other mirror then will be put in the treasure room. Today he takes that Yang mirror. If you don¡¯t want to get defeated, just go to the treasure room and get that Ying mirror.\\n\"\n\n\nmacro_GuiSetText(\"NPCSAY.npcsay\", claver)\nmacro_GuiSetWinVisable(\"NPCSAY\", 1)npc_id=macro_GetSeeNpcId()\nnpc_type=macro_GetSeeNpcType()\n\niaddmax=0\ntask_addid={\n{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},\n}\n\niawardmax=0\ntask_awardid={\n{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},{},\n}\n\ngc_fileExec(\".\\\\script\\\\public\\\\pub_see.lua\")\n\nnpc_id=macro_GetNow